[3] Borneo
Date: Sat 30 Jun 2012
Source: The Borneo Post [edited]
http://www.theborneopost.com/2012/06/30/hfmd-cases-on-the-increase-this-week/


HFMD cases on the increase this week
--------------------------------
KUCHING: The number of Hand, Foot and Mouth Disease (HFMD) cases have been on an increasing trend this week. A total of 341 new cases were reported from Sunday to Thursday (June 24 to 28). The divisions with the highest number of new cases were Kuching, Samarahan, Miri, Sarikei and Mukah. During the week, an increasing number of cases were noted in Sarikei, Mukah, Bintulu, and Limbang. As of Thursday, the cumulative number of cases stood at 8611.

This week, 31 clusters were reported involving 25 family clusters, three preschools, two primary schools and one childcare centre. Nine closure orders were served to preschools in Serian, Limbang, Sarikei, Miri, Dalat and Kota Samarahan.

The state Health Department called on the public to continuously practise personal hygiene especially hand-washing, seek medical treatment if their children have signs and symptoms of HFMD, limit outdoor activities and time spent in public places. This would also help prevent complications from the [atmospheric] haze.
Parents have also been asked not to send children with HFMD to childcare centres or any institution.

